The paper deals with the task of 3D face reconstruction from flat images, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which is a common theme in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper proposes a method for generating synthetic face datasets, which involves dealing with non-possible faces and preserving dataset diversity. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
